    "feat": {
        "name": "Smile at Failure",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "You know staying cool is key to prevailing in social situations, as anger leads to mistakes. When a creature you\u2019re interacting with decreases its attitude from indifferent to unfriendly or from unfriendly to hostile, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to any attempts to Make an Impression on the creature for the next hour. If this decrease in attitude leads to combat, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the subsequent initiative roll instead.",
